May 14 _ Thousands flock to the square to back the students. May 20 _ Martial law is declared in parts of Beijing. Long live democracy. Journalists and intellectuals join the protest. May 13 _ About 2000 students begin a hunger strike in Tiananmen Square. May 15 _ The government deadline for students to leave the square passes. April 27 _ More than 150000 students, with wide support from people on the street, surge past police lines and fill Tiananmen Square, chanting slogans for democracy and freedom. Coverage of the demonstrations is banned. May 25 _ Li makes his first appearance since declaring martial law. 